          <msContents>
            <summary>Collection of hymns, mantras, and praises to the Sun god (Āditya also called Sūrya) used for private or public recitation, meditation, and prayer. presented as a conversation between the legendary prince Arjuna and the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Ādityahṛdayastotra</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrībhaviṣyottara[pu]rāṇe śrīkṛṣṇārjjunasaṃvāde ādityahṛdayaṃ stotraṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // śubham astu // (f. 22v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
